Usually, a mapper is a group of different boards containing similar mapping hardware.<br />For example MMC1 is one mapper, but many boards (SAROM, SLROM, SKROM, SNROM, SOROM, SUROM, etc...)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Mon Sep 12, 2005 12:45 pm</p><hr />
